The modality segmentation into portable and stationary devices is pivotal in meeting the evolving healthcare needs. The portable devices segment is anticipated to grow rapidly due to technological advancements leading to the development of compact and lightweight extracorporeal life support devices. The convenience and flexibility offered by portable devices are increasingly preferred in critical care settings, enabling healthcare professionals to provide timely and efficient life-saving support to patients in need.

In terms of applications, the respiratory segment is likely to dominate the market as extracorporeal life support devices play a crucial role in managing acute respiratory failure. With the increasing prevalence of respiratory diseases globally, the demand for efficient respiratory support systems is on the rise, further propelling the growth of the market. Additionally, the cardiac and extracorporeal cardiopulmonary resuscitation (ECPR) segments are also significant contributors to the market, catering to cardiac-related emergencies and resuscitation needs.

The segmentation based on end users highlights the diverse settings where extracorporeal life support devices are utilized. The hospitals segment is expected to hold a significant market share due to the high volume of critical care admissions and surgical procedures performed in hospital settings. The presence of advanced medical facilities and skilled healthcare professionals in hospitals further augments the adoption of extracorporeal life support devices, driving market growth.

